<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-668] Controlled shutdown admin tool should not require controller JMX url/port to be supplied</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-668</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The controlled shutdown admin command takes a zookeeper string and also requires the user to supply the controller&apos;s jmx url/port. This is a bit annoying since the purpose of the zookeeper string is to discover the controller. The tool should require exactly one of these options. If zookeeper is supplied then discover the controller and its jmx port (which means we will need to add the jmx port information to zk).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
